wer of film and the art of migration against the apparent ahistoricity with which migration in Germany is addressed. She illustrates how the juridical category of »foreigner« is indeed as stubborn as it is socially misunderstood, yet how the cinema enacts not just the recognition (and failed recognition) services of this German immigration discourse - it portrays other negotiations of history and stories, genealogies and gender, iconoclastic controversies, transparency and veil, secularization, blood, sex, and skin.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aEmigration and immigration in motion pictures. 0aImmigrants in motion pictures. 0aMotion picturesxSocial aspectszGermany. 0aMotion pictureszGermanyxHistory. 4aGender. 4aKino. 4aMedien. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aMigration. 4aPolitik. 4aPostkolonialismus. 4aRassismus. 4aRepräsentationskritik. 4aVideo. 4aVisuelle Kultur. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh  aMedia Studies.  aMedia.  aMigration.  aPolitics.  aPostcolonialism.  aRacism.  aVideo.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2015z9783110438741oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783110401226oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839425756zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839425756423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839425756/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG P